    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@vvo that is in the right direction. Not naming the define() is the right way to go, I believe it is necessary for webpack, and has caused people some grief: https://github.com/webpack/webpack/issues/989\nThey fixed this when using webpack with the command you mentioned.\n\nI just need to figure out how to have my compiled js detect unnamed defines, and give them names at compile. I am not sure how to do this using requirejs. :(\n\nIn the future I will be migrating to webpack but for now I am using requirejs + almond.\n\nI've yet to try building from the source.\n",
