  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Unfortunately I've had to resort to doing this for the time being:\n\n```\nrequirejs: {\n      compile: {\n        options: {\n          baseUrl: '<%= config.jsDir %>',\n          mainConfigFile: '<%= config.jsDir %>/config.js',\n          name: 'main',\n          out: '<%= config.distDir %>/<%= config.jsDir %>/main.js',\n          paths: {\n            'jquery': 'empty:'\n          },\n          optimize: 'uglify2',\n          generateSourceMaps: true,\n          preserveLicenseComments: false,\n          onBuildRead: function (id, path, contents) {\n              if (id.indexOf('instant-search') === 0) {\n                  return contents.replace(/define\\(\\[\\], factory\\)/i, 'define(\"instant-search\", [], factory)');\n              } else {\n                  return contents;\n              }\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n```\n\nI'm doing a string replace on build of instantsearch's define().\n\nEventually when I migrate to webpack this will be a non-issue, but I wish I could figure out how to make requirejs notice instantsearch and name it appropriately on build.\n",
